    "The original image is then downsampled to the resolution required 16 × 16 for prediction.",
    "The image pixels are set to 1 at the locations where the lattice nodes are removed to represent the presence of a crack.",
    "In contrast, 0 valued pixels indicate the intact material domain.",
    "The following figure (Fig. 2) shows some ground-truth images for the corresponding 2D plate samples.",
    "The dataset consists of randomly generated samples in the same 2D domain, with a single, straight crack of random length, location, and orientation."
